FBIS3-49411 "dreeu007_d_94003" FBIS-EEU-94-007 Document Type:Daily Report 11 Jan 1994 SLOVAKIA Kovac Discusses Minority Policy With Hungarians LD0701204194 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network in Slovak 1730 GMT 7 Jan 94 LD0701204194 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network in Slovak 1730 GMT 7 Jan 94 Language: Slovak Article Type:BFN [Text] In Bratislava this afternoon, Slovak President Michal Kovac received for the first time personally representatives of the Hungarian Civic Party [HCP]. Anton Bodis, the president's spokesman, will now tell us about the preliminary results of that meeting. He is at this moment on the other end of the telephone line. Good evening. Can one already talk about some specific conclusions from that meeting? [Bodis] Good evening. HCP Chairman Laszlo Nagy briefed the president about the proposals, which his party sees as being possible ways of improving the position of national minorities in Slovakia. The final conclusions will be known as soon as the president has studied these proposals in greater detail. The HCP chairman also briefed the president about the party's attitude to tomorrow's meeting in Komarno. The president voiced the hope that the meeting will take place in a calm and nonconfrontational tone. Michal Kovac appreciated the realistic and tolerant attitude adopted by the HCP to relations between Slovaks and the Hungarian national minority, and toward ways of improving them. Both sides agreed on the need to outline the national policy of the Slovak Republic and ways of implementing it.
